# React components

- Functional components + hooks; no class components.
- Props via TypeScript interfaces; use `Readonly<{...}>` where appropriate.
- Separate presentation (`components/`) from page composition (`app/` routes).

## Reuse

- Reusable UI in `components/ui/` — no duplicate Button/Input per feature.
- Extract hooks/components only on real repetition; no premature abstraction.

## Accessibility

- Semantic HTML: `main`, `nav`, `button` (no `div` as a clickable button).
- `aria-label` where visible text is missing.
- Do not forget focus states (`focus-visible:outline-*`).

## Example

```tsx
interface CardProps {
  title: string;
  children: React.ReactNode;
}

export function Card({ title, children }: Readonly<CardProps>) {
  return (
    <section className="rounded-lg border p-6">
      <h2 className="text-lg font-medium">{title}</h2>
      {children}
    </section>
  );
}
```
